      "writtenOn": "2020-12-16T18:16:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We need to pretend that we don\u0027t know the details of UText, i.e. treat it as an \"incomplete type\" (see the errors in https://googleplex-android-review.git.corp.google.com/c/platform/external/skia/+/13161147/1#message-9558875f3df1af96b0c28f8df7874a914a8c61f6). So if we needed it, this would be a pointer to UText, and we\u0027d need to call the method that closes it (I think \"utext_close\"?) in the destructor.\n\nThat said, you don\u0027t actually need this. You pass it to utext_openUTF8, but you can just pass nullptr, like you do in other call sites.",
